[{'action': 'opened', 'author': 'willpaige', 'comment_id': None, 'datetime': '2016-06-23 08:09:02+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': "I've got 3 production sties that were using instafeed with out any issues. Until a couple of weeks ago when I now get 'Uncaught Error: Error from Instagram: The access_token provided is invalid.' 

I haven't changed anything and my instagram clients are the same.

http://willpowerfitness.co.uk/
http://botanyblend.com/", 'title': 'Uncaught Error: Error from Instagram: The access_token provided is invalid.', 'type': 'issue'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'edinchez', 'comment_id': 228087073.0, 'datetime': '2016-06-23 15:26:55+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': "I think Instagram changed their API on June 1. So until instafeed.js gets updated it probably won't work.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'NicolasVanhecke', 'comment_id': 228308629.0, 'datetime': '2016-06-24 10:10:36+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_2', 'text': 'Yep same thing.. got this running on a few live sites. Any word on an update?', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'KingScooty', 'comment_id': 228533255.0, 'datetime': '2016-06-25 11:12:21+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_3', 'text': 'This is nuts. There was a fix for this in the issues, and even that seems to be resetting at the moment. Really could do with this getting fixed.', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'amandeepsinghvirdi', 'comment_id': 228674645.0, 'datetime': '2016-06-27 07:41:37+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_4', 'text': 'Follow the instructions from to create access token using the correct client id and it should fix the issue

https://www.instagram.com/developer/authentication/', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'NicolasVanhecke', 'comment_id': 228697776.0, 'datetime': '2016-06-27 09:35:01+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_2', 'text': "This will not work when my app is still in Sandbox mode right? How long does this usually take? (I'm am working on a project from another developer who is not working at my firm anymore.. don't know his app_id en client_id and stuff.. So i had to create a new one)", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'emersonthis', 'comment_id': 230623944.0, 'datetime': '2016-07-05 22:42:13+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_5', 'text': "^ @username_4 's tip works but you'll need to update the client settings so that `https://elfsight.com/service/generate-instagram-access-token/ ` is included in as one of the redirect URLs.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'emersonthis', 'comment_id': 230632831.0, 'datetime': '2016-07-05 23:30:43+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_5', 'text': "Does anyone know if *any* requests still allow the client_id to authenticate? I have yet to find one that didn't auth error without an auth token.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'marza91', 'comment_id': 230698575.0, 'datetime': '2016-07-06 07:29:16+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_6', 'text': "I can't authenticate using client ID only either. We're only using this library to display a feed of tagged images without any login required, so it's not really possible for me to store an access token in a secure way.. I don't believe it's considered safe to just generate a token with my own user and paste this in the js-file..?", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'emersonthis', 'comment_id': 230828256.0, 'datetime': '2016-07-06 16:30:23+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_5', 'text': 'That's precisely what I did. It's definitely not ideal but the sandbox token has no permissions so I'm not sure if it's "unsafe" or just a pain in the ass. 

>', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'marza91', 'comment_id': 230862557.0, 'datetime': '2016-07-06 18:29:41+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_6', 'text': "Yes, I tried with the sandbox version with auth token as well, but I needed all pictures from a tag, which of course wouldn't work.
I'm not sure how the verification process works around this, but maybe it would be possible to create and verify a common user/client for use in instafeed.is? So that we all could use the same access token, but there's no content/images on the account?", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'emersonthis', 'comment_id': 230863050.0, 'datetime': '2016-07-06 18:32:26+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_5', 'text': 'We’d slam into rate limits pretty fast if any substantive group of people started using it. If memory serves, we now get 500 requests/hour, which is fine for modest sites, but easily reachable with “crowd sourcing”.


>', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'marza91', 'comment_id': 230864876.0, 'datetime': '2016-07-06 18:38:18+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_6', 'text': 'Ah, I see, that's too bad. Seems to me like instagram don't want us to show image feeds on other sites anymore.. Which also seems like a "shoot yourself in the foot" kind of thing to do...', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'emersonthis', 'comment_id': 230865655.0, 'datetime': '2016-07-06 18:40:50+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_5', 'text': 'That’s 100% their intention. This move was entirely calculated with the goal of quashing “unapproved” glimpses of the Ig user experience.

>', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}]

